      <section eId="sec_CC-573">
        <num>CC 573</num>
        <heading>573. Â Dispensation of security</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-573__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Security is dispensed with when any of the following occur:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CC-573__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A person has a legal usufruct under Article 223 or 3252.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CC-573__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A surviving spouse has a legal usufruct under Article 890 unless the naked owner is not a child of the usufructuary or if the naked owner is a child of the usufructuary and is also a forced heir of the decedent, the naked owner may obtain security but only to the extent of his legitime.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CC-573__subsec_A__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A parent has a legal usufruct under Article 891 unless the naked owner is not a child of the usufructuary.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CC-573__subsec_A__subsec_4">
            <num>(4)</num>
            <content>
              <p>A surviving spouse has a legal usufruct under Article 2434 unless the naked owner is a child of the decedent but not a child of the usufructuary.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-573__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A seller or donor of property under reservation of usufruct is not required to give security.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110763</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
